    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re "Yes, Writing English Is a Process. And It's Easy" (letter, March 18):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re "Yes, Writing English Is a Process. And It's Easy" (letter, March 18):</p>
        <p>Janet M. Garnier's defense of "pedagogical molasses" would be hilarious if it weren't so defiantly wrongheaded.</p>
        <p>Why should the writers of the national standards for teaching English speak in a "language comprehensible" only to a "specific audience," which Ms. Garnier identifies as educators?</p>
        <p>Why can't we just agree that the national standard for teaching English shall be the wonderful "Elements of Style" by William Strunk Jr. and E. B. White? It is on the desk of everyone I know who values communication.</p>
        <p>JOHN H. CLEVELAND 3D Montclair, N.J., March 18, 1996</p>
      </block>
